When he died, I mean,
my dad moved my car keys

00:37:08.540 --> 00:37:09.830 align:middle line:90%
across the table.

00:37:09.830 --> 00:37:13.310 align:middle line:84%
He turned people's
windshield wipers on.

00:37:13.310 --> 00:37:16.670 align:middle line:84%
People would see he's still
an amazingly active spirit,

00:37:16.670 --> 00:37:19.490 align:middle line:84%
and it's because he was
training for the last year

00:37:19.490 --> 00:37:21.890 align:middle line:84%
and a half of his life
on-- because he also

00:37:21.890 --> 00:37:22.950 align:middle line:90%
was a communicator.

00:37:22.950 --> 00:37:26.640 align:middle line:84%
So he was like, I'm going
to be able to communicate.

00:37:26.640 --> 00:37:29.253 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So we only
have a few minutes left,

00:37:29.253 --> 00:37:30.420 align:middle line:90%
and I want to get into this.

00:37:30.420 --> 00:37:33.800 align:middle line:84%
Some people are afraid because
of some of, maybe, the things

00:37:33.800 --> 00:37:35.570 align:middle line:84%
they've experienced
in life or done,

00:37:35.570 --> 00:37:39.060 align:middle line:84%
that they're going to be
met with evil entities.

00:37:39.060 --> 00:37:41.030 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about
what your experience is

00:37:41.030 --> 00:37:42.530 align:middle line:90%
in truth with that.

00:37:42.530 --> 00:37:46.880 align:middle line:84%
>>SALICROW: I have never met
anybody who's been to hell.

00:37:46.880 --> 00:37:49.640 align:middle line:84%
I've never really-- I have
experienced evil entities,

00:37:49.640 --> 00:37:52.400 align:middle line:84%
but not in everyday
spirit communication.

00:37:52.400 --> 00:37:54.770 align:middle line:84%
That's usually a
much different story.

00:37:54.770 --> 00:37:58.800 align:middle line:84%
But people, in general, have
spirits that look out for them.

00:37:58.800 --> 00:38:01.262 align:middle line:84%
And when we cross,
we're not met by evil.

00:38:01.262 --> 00:38:02.345 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: We're protected.

00:38:02.345 --> 00:38:03.512 align:middle line:90%
>>SALICROW: We're protected.

00:38:03.512 --> 00:38:06.230 align:middle line:84%
If we have a lot of
garbage around our life

00:38:06.230 --> 00:38:09.380 align:middle line:84%
at the end of our passing,
things that we didn't process,

00:38:09.380 --> 00:38:13.400 align:middle line:84%
we're going to spend more time
in reflection than somebody who

00:38:13.400 --> 00:38:15.500 align:middle line:90%
maybe worked on that in life.

00:38:15.500 --> 00:38:19.640 align:middle line:84%
But as a general rule,
I tell people, again,

00:38:19.640 --> 00:38:26.360 align:middle line:84%
it goes back to the media about
exaggerating negative entities.

00:38:26.360 --> 00:38:27.260 align:middle line:90%
They are there.

00:38:27.260 --> 00:38:29.660 align:middle line:84%
But there's also negative
people around the world,

00:38:29.660 --> 00:38:31.743 align:middle line:84%
but there's a lot
more good people.

00:38:31.743 --> 00:38:34.160 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Turn on the TV,
you're being bathed in negative.

00:38:34.160 --> 00:38:34.790 align:middle line:90%
>>SALICROW: Exactly.

00:38:34.790 --> 00:38:37.332 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So one more thing that
probably feeds in with that,

00:38:37.332 --> 00:38:38.750 align:middle line:84%
and that's the
notion of a timeout

00:38:38.750 --> 00:38:39.860 align:middle line:84%
that you talk
about in your book.

00:38:39.860 --> 00:38:40.760 align:middle line:90%
>>SALICROW: Yes.

00:38:40.760 --> 00:38:45.800 align:middle line:84%
So timeout is when people
have taken their own life,

00:38:45.800 --> 00:38:48.980 align:middle line:84%
when they've passed
through suicide,

00:38:48.980 --> 00:38:51.147 align:middle line:84%
or sometimes when
people have passed

00:38:51.147 --> 00:38:53.480 align:middle line:84%
at the hands of other people
because they're overwhelmed

00:38:53.480 --> 00:38:57.560 align:middle line:84%
by their experience, or if
they've done a lot of really

00:38:57.560 --> 00:38:59.180 align:middle line:90%
bad things in their life.

00:38:59.180 --> 00:39:01.700 align:middle line:84%
They're going to go into
what I call timeout,

00:39:01.700 --> 00:39:04.550 align:middle line:84%
and it's like sending a kid
to the timeout chair when they

00:39:04.550 --> 00:39:09.230 align:middle line:84%
have to reflect on their actions
and see what brought it about,

00:39:09.230 --> 00:39:12.270 align:middle line:84%
what went wrong, how people
really feel about them.

00:39:12.270 --> 00:39:15.020 align:middle line:84%
So even when somebody
has had a lot

00:39:15.020 --> 00:39:18.480 align:middle line:84%
of things to be
regretful of in passing,

00:39:18.480 --> 00:39:19.610 align:middle line:90%
they're not being tortured.

00:39:19.610 --> 00:39:21.277 align:middle line:84%
They're being put
into this place, where

00:39:21.277 --> 00:39:23.000 align:middle line:90%
their emotions are turned down.

00:39:23.000 --> 00:39:26.120 align:middle line:84%
They're reviewing their life,
not only from their angle,

00:39:26.120 --> 00:39:28.160 align:middle line:90%
but other people's angles.

00:39:28.160 --> 00:39:31.880 align:middle line:84%
And they're getting to see
where things went wrong.

00:39:31.880 --> 00:39:32.990 align:middle line:90%
And they're healing.

00:39:32.990 --> 00:39:35.040 align:middle line:84%
And we can still-- this
is one of the reasons,

00:39:35.040 --> 00:39:38.390 align:middle line:84%
again, why ancestor altars
are helpful is, we can still

00:39:38.390 --> 00:39:40.460 align:middle line:84%
contribute to our
loved one's healing,

00:39:40.460 --> 00:39:44.190 align:middle line:84%
even after they have
passed, by healing ourselves

00:39:44.190 --> 00:39:48.510 align:middle line:84%
and also by sending them
prayers, and love, and Reiki,

00:39:48.510 --> 00:39:51.150 align:middle line:84%
or setting up an altar
and giving them offerings,

00:39:51.150 --> 00:39:53.670 align:middle line:84%
and making sure they
know that you love them,

00:39:53.670 --> 00:39:56.110 align:middle line:84%
you forgive them, that you're
still praying for them.

00:39:56.110 --> 00:39:56.910 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:39:56.910 --> 00:39:58.330 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for that.

00:39:58.330 --> 00:40:01.830 align:middle line:90%
And final question.

00:40:01.830 --> 00:40:05.940 align:middle line:84%
Do you see a time coming, like
an almost utopian, Elysian

00:40:05.940 --> 00:40:10.320 align:middle line:84%
Fields view of life,
where we choose our time--

00:40:10.320 --> 00:40:13.290 align:middle line:84%
and there's a beautiful,
beautiful story

00:40:13.290 --> 00:40:15.750 align:middle line:84%
of this in some of
Gates McKibben's works,

00:40:15.750 --> 00:40:17.700 align:middle line:84%
where she talks about
these characters

00:40:17.700 --> 00:40:20.040 align:middle line:84%
through three books,
called Grace and Luke that

00:40:20.040 --> 00:40:22.800 align:middle line:84%
keep incarnating together,
but very consciously.

00:40:22.800 --> 00:40:25.350 align:middle line:84%
And that at the end of their
life, they go off in the field

00:40:25.350 --> 00:40:27.310 align:middle line:84%
together when they're
old and they're done.

00:40:27.310 --> 00:40:28.110 align:middle line:90%
And they choose--

00:40:28.110 --> 00:40:29.970 align:middle line:84%
>>SALICROW: I've met people who
can do that, who've done that,

00:40:29.970 --> 00:40:30.770 align:middle line:90%
who really--

00:40:30.770 --> 00:40:32.790 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Tell us about
that beautiful thing

00:40:32.790 --> 00:40:33.810 align:middle line:90%
before we say goodbye.

00:40:33.810 --> 00:40:34.610 align:middle line:90%
>>SALICROW: Yeah.

00:40:34.610 --> 00:40:37.590 align:middle line:84%
So I've met people,
who, well, have

00:40:37.590 --> 00:40:40.650 align:middle line:84%
made the conscious decision
to let themselves go.

00:40:40.650 --> 00:40:43.020 align:middle line:84%
They were usually
were sick, so it's not

00:40:43.020 --> 00:40:45.990 align:middle line:84%
like they were in perfect
health and decided that was it.

00:40:45.990 --> 00:40:49.440 align:middle line:84%
But they were usually
pretty spiritual people.

00:40:49.440 --> 00:40:52.473 align:middle line:84%
So I don't think it's an easily
achieved thing for people

00:40:52.473 --> 00:40:54.390 align:middle line:84%
because I think fear is
one of the things that

00:40:54.390 --> 00:40:56.250 align:middle line:90%
gets in the way.

00:40:56.250 --> 00:40:59.430 align:middle line:84%
But my grandmother was
an example of that.

00:40:59.430 --> 00:41:02.710 align:middle line:84%
She was going to be
moved into a nursing home

00:41:02.710 --> 00:41:05.293 align:middle line:84%
because she had this infection
in her foot that couldn't heal,

00:41:05.293 --> 00:41:06.585 align:middle line:90%
and she was just getting older.

00:41:06.585 --> 00:41:07.690 align:middle line:90%
She was 84.

00:41:07.690 --> 00:41:11.020 align:middle line:84%
And she had always said
that she would never

00:41:11.020 --> 00:41:12.880 align:middle line:84%
go to a nursing home,
and she literally

00:41:12.880 --> 00:41:15.970 align:middle line:84%
died the night before she was
going to go to a nursing home.

00:41:15.970 --> 00:41:17.050 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: There you go.

00:41:17.050 --> 00:41:19.180 align:middle line:84%
My mother died
suddenly, and she said,

00:41:19.180 --> 00:41:22.210 align:middle line:84%
I would rather be dead than
see that man in office.

00:41:22.210 --> 00:41:24.640 align:middle line:84%
And she did not want to see
Bill Clinton take office

00:41:24.640 --> 00:41:26.950 align:middle line:84%
and died 15 minutes
before midnight

00:41:26.950 --> 00:41:29.110 align:middle line:84%
of an unexpected stroke
before his inauguration.

00:41:29.110 --> 00:41:30.610 align:middle line:84%
>>SALICROW: Because
it was something

00:41:30.610 --> 00:41:32.278 align:middle line:84%
that she had made
a decision about.

00:41:32.278 --> 00:41:33.820 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And I
think even my father.

00:41:33.820 --> 00:41:36.460 align:middle line:84%
Because just the
day before things

00:41:36.460 --> 00:41:38.405 align:middle line:84%
went south really
quickly, there was

00:41:38.405 --> 00:41:40.780 align:middle line:84%
starting to look like there
was some dementia setting in,

00:41:40.780 --> 00:41:42.830 align:middle line:84%
and he did not want to
live without his mind.

00:41:42.830 --> 00:41:43.630 align:middle line:90%
Boom.

00:41:43.630 --> 00:41:46.660 align:middle line:84%
The next day, he's in the
ER, unconscious, and gone.

00:41:46.660 --> 00:41:49.490 align:middle line:84%
And so, I think they were
both conscious in that way,

00:41:49.490 --> 00:41:50.780 align:middle line:90%
which is really beautiful.

00:41:50.780 --> 00:41:51.640 align:middle line:90%
>>SALICROW: It is beautiful.

00:41:51.640 --> 00:41:53.380 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You don't want to
see someone lingering in a life

00:41:53.380 --> 00:41:54.770 align:middle line:90%
they don't want out of fear.

00:41:54.770 --> 00:41:56.620 align:middle line:90%
So that's a note for all of us.

00:41:56.620 --> 00:42:00.580 align:middle line:84%
Do the very best we can, getting
through and managing emotions,

00:42:00.580 --> 00:42:03.810 align:middle line:84%
find a good practice, find
people that we can talk to.

00:42:03.810 --> 00:42:05.400 align:middle line:90%
What else would you add to that?

00:42:05.400 --> 00:42:09.330 align:middle line:84%
>>SALICROW: I would recommend
that people talk to their dead.

00:42:09.330 --> 00:42:12.510 align:middle line:10%
Because our dead can hear
us, see us, experience.

00:42:12.510 --> 00:42:14.490 align:middle line:10%
I describe it like
a police mirror.

00:42:14.490 --> 00:42:17.850 align:middle line:84%
The dead are on the side,
that they can hear us, see us.

00:42:17.850 --> 00:42:20.460 align:middle line:84%
They have a hard time getting
us to hear or see them.

00:42:20.460 --> 00:42:21.960 align:middle line:84%
And the mediums,
the person who can

00:42:21.960 --> 00:42:23.725 align:middle line:84%
walk between the
rooms going, hey,

00:42:23.725 --> 00:42:25.350 align:middle line:84%
this is what they're
saying over there.

00:42:25.350 --> 00:42:26.310 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:42:26.310 --> 00:42:27.310 align:middle line:90%
Perfect.

00:42:27.310 --> 00:42:28.110 align:middle line:90%
Final thought?

00:42:28.110 --> 00:42:29.130 align:middle line:90%
Is that it?

00:42:29.130 --> 00:42:30.900 align:middle line:10%
>>SALICROW: My final
thought is that we

00:42:30.900 --> 00:42:33.040 align:middle line:10%
need to prepare
ourselves for death,

00:42:33.040 --> 00:42:35.550 align:middle line:10%
and we need to become
comfortable with it

00:42:35.550 --> 00:42:37.830 align:middle line:10%
and educate ourselves
about it because it's

00:42:37.830 --> 00:42:39.960 align:middle line:10%
going to happen to us all.

00:42:39.960 --> 00:42:40.760 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Indeed.

00:42:40.760 --> 00:42:43.810 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much for such a
beautiful and intimate glimpse

00:42:43.810 --> 00:42:46.313 align:middle line:84%
into something that
awaits all of us.

00:42:46.313 --> 00:42:47.230 align:middle line:90%
>>SALICROW: Thank you.

00:42:47.230 --> 00:42:48.298 align:middle line:90%
I appreciate it.

00:42:48.298 --> 00:42:49.840 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Again,
the name of the book

00:42:49.840 --> 00:42:52.930 align:middle line:10%
